Final written examination on theory and practice
A- test questions are answered with maximum precision and reference to corresponding theoretical sources and are supported by references to the sample text; morphological/syntactic  text analysis follows rules and requirements fully
B- test questions are answered correctly and demonstrate very good knowledge of theoretical aspects and reference to the sample text; morphological/ syntactic text analysis follows rules and requirements fully;
C- test questions are answered with various degrees of precision and demonstrate good knowledge of theoretical aspects and are supported by references to the sample text; morphological/syntactic text analysis follows key rules and requirements;
D- answers to test questions show the student's satisfactory knowledge of some theoretical aspects and do not have any support by example from the sample text; morphological/syntactic text analysis follows rules and requirements satisfactory;
E- test answers demonstrate student's knowledge of some basic principles of morphological/syntactic text analysis; morphological/syntactic text analysis follows some basic rules and requirements.
